            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-06-16T04:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-06-16T04:00:00-05:00" n="806" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d806">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">693.0031/6–1649: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the united Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Douglas</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-06-16T10:00:00+01:00">June 16, 1949—10 a. m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 10:08 a. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2314. Foreign Office prepared discuss export controls China with Martin (Deptel
                    2010, June 11) but June 21 earliest feasible date. British representative will
                    be Morland, Counselor Economic Relations Department.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Douglas</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
